  "prompt": "How can I dress for a foam party?",
  "response": "A foam party is all about fun and getting soaked! Here's a breakdown of how to dress appropriately:\n\n**Priorities:**\n\n*   **Comfort:** You'll be moving, dancing, and possibly slipping and sliding.\n*   **Quick-Drying:** Think materials that won't weigh you down when wet.\n*   **Minimal Clothing:** Less is more (within reason and the party's dress code, if any).\n*   **Protection:** Consider eye protection and protection for your skin.\n*   **Not Too Precious:** Don't wear anything you're deeply attached to or that's dry-clean only.\n\n**Clothing Options:**\n\n*   **Swimsuits:** The most obvious choice! Bikinis, one-pieces, swim trunks - whatever you're comfortable in.\n*   **Athletic Wear:** Think sports bras, tank tops, shorts, leggings. Look for moisture-wicking materials.\n*   **Old Clothes:** Items you don't mind getting stained or slightly damaged.\n*   **Neon/Bright Colors:** Foam parties often have a vibrant atmosphere, so bright colors fit right in.\n\n**Clothing to AVOID:**\n\n*   **Jeans:** They'll become heavy and uncomfortable when wet.\n*   **Anything White or Delicate:** The foam may contain dyes that could stain.\n*   **Expensive Clothing:** Save your good stuff for another occasion.\n*   **Long, Flowing Clothing:** A tripping hazard waiting to happen.\n\n**Footwear:**\n\n*   **Flip-Flops/Sandals:** Easy to slip on and off, and they dry quickly.\n*   **Water Shoes:** Provide better grip and protect your feet from rough surfaces.\n*   **Barefoot (check the venue rules):** Some venues might allow this, but be careful of slippery surfaces and potential hazards.\n*   **AVOID:** Sneakers, boots, or anything that will get waterlogged.\n\n**Accessories:**\n\n*   **Waterproof Phone Case/Bag:** Essential to protect your phone.\n*   **Sunglasses/Goggles:** Protect your eyes from the foam, which can sometimes be irritating.\n*   **Hat/Bandana:** Can help keep foam out of your hair.\n*   **Waterproof Makeup:** If you choose to wear makeup, opt for waterproof options.\n*   **Hair Ties:** To keep your hair out of your face.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Venue Rules:** Check with the venue beforehand to see if there are any specific dress code requirements or restrictions.\n*   **Weather:** If it's chilly, consider a quick-drying cover-up like a rash guard or light jacket.\n*   **Skin Sensitivity:** If you have sensitive skin, you might want to test a small area with the foam beforehand to check for any reactions.\n*   **Pre-Treat Stains:** As soon as possible after the party, pre-treat any potential stains on your clothes.\n\n**Example Outfits:**\n\n*   **Option 1:** Swimsuit + Flip-Flops + Waterproof Phone Case + Sunglasses\n*   **Option 2:** Neon Tank Top + Athletic Shorts + Water Shoes + Hair Tie\n*   **Option 3:** Old T-shirt + Swim Trunks + Flip-Flops + Hat\n\n**Key Takeaway:**  Dress comfortably, practically, and be prepared to get wet! Have fun!\n",
